Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.67,0:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,just left it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.18,0:42:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We moved it to the current
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.80,0:42:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,version of the OS so that we
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.31,0:42:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,could take advantage of what
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.45,0:42:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.53,0:42:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying current and staying
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.09,0:42:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,state-of-the-art, is just as
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.83,0:42:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,important as adding new
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.64,0:42:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.91,0:42:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to add new
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.00,0:42:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,features just to add them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.19,0:42:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we did was, we added
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.53,0:42:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,support for the extra-large
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.04,0:42:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,complication that was now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.38,0:42:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,offered in watchOS 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.38,0:42:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's funny, when I put this
